## 📝 Project Report

**Platforms Used:** HackerRank and Google Workspace (Forms/Sheets).

For the coding practice component, I used **HackerRank** to complete a beginner-level algorithmic challenge. This platform is invaluable for students because it provides a structured environment to master Data Structures and Algorithms, which are critical for technical interviews. It allows for consistent skill-tracking through badges and leaderboards.

For the collaboration component, I developed a **Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz** using **Google Forms** and integrated it with **Google Sheets** for automated data collection. These tools are essential for academic research and peer collaboration, enabling the efficient gathering and analysis of data in real-time. By linking the form to a spreadsheet, I can instantly visualize common knowledge gaps among my batchmates regarding digital safety.

Using these tools over the next few years will help me maintain technical rigor and organize project data more professionally. HackerRank will ensure I am industry-ready for FAANG placements, while proficiency in Google Workspace will allow me to manage complex team projects and community outreach effectively as a Digital Ambassador.

